The weather's nice today.

00:20:35.881 --> 00:20:36.798
Who…

00:20:37.382 --> 00:20:38.884
Who talks about the weather?

00:20:38.967 --> 00:20:42.429
Talking about the weather
is an icebreaker.

00:20:42.512 --> 00:20:44.639
That would make things even more awkward.

00:20:44.723 --> 00:20:47.768
Isn't it better to ask something
like if they have eaten?

00:20:48.393 --> 00:20:50.479
-They could ask if the ride was okay.
-Okay, then.

00:20:50.562 --> 00:20:53.732
Try acting like the high-ranking person
and ask about my meal.

00:20:55.192 --> 00:20:56.151
Hey, there.

00:20:56.777 --> 00:20:59.071
I'm Kang Tae-poong from Typhoon Trading.

00:20:59.154 --> 00:21:00.614
Have you eaten?

00:21:01.948 --> 00:21:04.076
Wasn't the road slippery at all?

00:21:04.159 --> 00:21:05.827
Which company are you from again?

00:21:05.911 --> 00:21:08.413
-Where is it?
-It's Typhoon Trading.

00:21:08.497 --> 00:21:14.044
EPISODE 5
HEAVEN, WHERE WE ARE

00:21:33.855 --> 00:21:35.399
That almost started a fire.

00:21:46.451 --> 00:21:47.411
I'll also

00:21:48.328 --> 00:21:50.622
take two spoons of sugar and cream.

00:22:03.176 --> 00:22:04.553
She must've been exhausted.

00:22:20.569 --> 00:22:21.862
You're here.

00:22:22.904 --> 00:22:24.156
You should've gone home.

00:22:24.239 --> 00:22:28.118
-I think Ms. Oh is really tired.
-What?

00:22:32.747 --> 00:22:34.374
-What the heck?!
-Oh, my gosh.

00:22:34.457 --> 00:22:37.169
You made the main character wait.

00:22:37.878 --> 00:22:38.879
Mr. Bae?

00:22:40.380 --> 00:22:41.214
You know…

00:22:44.467 --> 00:22:46.761
I wanted to live
an unremarkable life, Tae-soo.

00:22:46.845 --> 00:22:48.013
It's Tae-poong.

00:22:50.056 --> 00:22:51.349
What's that sound?

00:22:52.559 --> 00:22:54.769
Did you turn on the computer, Mr. Bae?

00:22:54.853 --> 00:22:57.272
As expected of Romi… I mean, Ms. Oh.

00:22:57.355 --> 00:22:58.857
You follow my every move.

00:22:58.940 --> 00:23:00.692
She's a senior staff now.

00:23:03.570 --> 00:23:07.032
-Why are you here?
-My feet just led me here.

00:23:07.741 --> 00:23:08.950
CUSTOMS BROKER EXAM

00:23:09.034 --> 00:23:09.951
Customs Broker?

00:23:10.785 --> 00:23:13.872
-You want to study here?
-No, I'll study at a prep school.

00:23:13.955 --> 00:23:17.417
-This place is for rest and recharging.
-Why?

00:23:18.335 --> 00:23:19.920
Mr. Kang said we were family.

00:23:26.468 --> 00:23:28.303
You came to use the computer, right?

00:23:32.015 --> 00:23:34.476
You're asking
too many questions today, Ms. Oh.

00:23:34.559 --> 00:23:36.269
That's all for today.

00:23:36.353 --> 00:23:39.189
-You'd better pay for electricity.
-But we're family.

00:23:41.691 --> 00:23:44.361
No, we're not.
And bring your own toilet paper.

00:23:45.487 --> 00:23:47.864
This is abuse!

00:23:47.948 --> 00:23:50.575
Mr. Kang, please say something.
This isn't right.

00:23:50.659 --> 00:23:51.826
What is this?

00:23:51.910 --> 00:23:53.787
Why do you have this menu?

00:23:53.870 --> 00:23:55.538
When did you sneak a look?

00:23:56.373 --> 00:23:57.249
No, I…

00:23:57.332 --> 00:23:59.542
I know you're interested in me.

00:23:59.626 --> 00:24:02.837
-But you can't go through someone's bag--
-We worked hard to collect this.

00:24:02.921 --> 00:24:05.924
-You can't just take it for yourself.
-Give it back.

00:24:06.007 --> 00:24:07.384
What else did you take?

00:24:07.467 --> 00:24:10.011
-Let me see your bag.
-Hey!

00:24:10.095 --> 00:24:11.805
-Did you take--
-Mr. Kang!

00:24:11.888 --> 00:24:13.306
-Come on, Ms. Oh.
-Seriously?

00:24:13.390 --> 00:24:15.934
-Make your own coffee too.
-Coffee?

00:24:16.017 --> 00:24:19.104
-Fine, I won't drink it.
-We don't have enough for you.

00:24:33.201 --> 00:24:35.245
-Are you leaving already?
-I'm sorry.

00:24:35.328 --> 00:24:38.290
Everything's ready.
You should eat before you go.

00:24:38.373 --> 00:24:41.167
Sorry, I need to catch the train.
You go ahead.

00:24:41.251 --> 00:24:42.252
Tae-poong,

00:24:43.128 --> 00:24:45.505
good luck at work today.

00:24:45.588 --> 00:24:47.173
Don't rush around, okay?

00:24:47.257 --> 00:24:48.383
I won't.

00:24:49.134 --> 00:24:52.637
It's my first day
bringing in the goods I signed for.

00:24:52.721 --> 00:24:55.974
I already showed it to over ten places,
and some of them showed interest.

00:24:57.726 --> 00:25:01.479
I did such a great job raising my son.

00:25:01.563 --> 00:25:02.647
My son.

00:25:03.398 --> 00:25:06.735
After I receive all the items today,
we'll have a delicious dinner.

00:25:06.818 --> 00:25:09.612
We were supposed
to go to Nam-mo's chicken place.

00:25:10.488 --> 00:25:11.489
I almost forgot.

00:25:13.366 --> 00:25:14.451
Then…

00:25:15.827 --> 00:25:18.496
Let's go eat steak
once I sell all the safety shoes.

00:25:19.331 --> 00:25:20.623
That sounds wonderful.

00:25:23.460 --> 00:25:24.461
And, Mom…

00:25:27.422 --> 00:25:28.798
I promise I'll get it back.

00:25:31.009 --> 00:25:33.261
I'll get our home back no matter what.

00:25:47.734 --> 00:25:48.818
What's this?

00:25:50.779 --> 00:25:53.740
-It's fried eggs.
-It looks yummy.

00:25:55.116 --> 00:25:57.118
-Can I have it?
-No.

00:25:59.329 --> 00:26:01.956
It's gone cold. I'll make you a new one.

00:26:03.249 --> 00:26:04.501
Come on.

00:26:07.379 --> 00:26:11.007
You can head inside over there,
and feel free to look around.

00:26:12.342 --> 00:26:14.886
Please look this over and sign it.

00:26:16.513 --> 00:26:20.141
DATE OF RECEIPT,
ITEM AND QUANTITY

00:26:22.394 --> 00:26:24.437
-The products are coming from Pusan?
-Yes.

00:26:26.356 --> 00:26:28.191
That's going to take a long time.

00:26:28.274 --> 00:26:29.609
REPRESENTATIVE: OH MI-SEON

00:26:29.692 --> 00:26:31.111
I'm going to wait here.

00:26:32.153 --> 00:26:33.655
-Thank you.
-No problem.

00:26:50.922 --> 00:26:52.340
-Is this the place?
-Yes.

00:26:57.220 --> 00:26:58.179
Isn't it great?

00:27:02.517 --> 00:27:03.435
This way.

00:27:10.942 --> 00:27:13.194
What is it?
Why are you just standing there?

00:27:20.285 --> 00:27:22.579
Wait. They were here before.

00:27:27.625 --> 00:27:30.837
Look. This place is completely empty!

00:27:36.009 --> 00:27:37.677
There's no electricity, either.

00:27:44.517 --> 00:27:46.853
All the items were here.

00:27:48.188 --> 00:27:51.274
I knew it smelled fishy.
We've been scammed.

00:27:51.357 --> 00:27:53.234
-I told you so!
-It was here.

00:27:53.318 --> 00:27:55.236
-When did they switch it?
-Hold on.

00:27:56.237 --> 00:27:57.071
Wait a minute.

00:27:59.115 --> 00:28:00.241
Kang Tae-poong!

00:28:04.704 --> 00:28:05.622
Mr. Park!

00:28:07.290 --> 00:28:08.791
Open the door, Mr. Park!

00:28:27.060 --> 00:28:28.394
Kang Tae-poong!

00:28:28.478 --> 00:28:30.855
You'll hurt yourself!

00:28:31.689 --> 00:28:32.649
Gosh.

00:28:42.075 --> 00:28:43.284
Mr. Park!

00:28:57.590 --> 00:29:00.969
-There's no way he's here. He ran away.
-He has to be here.

00:29:01.928 --> 00:29:03.429
He's not here!

00:29:11.479 --> 00:29:12.480
Mr. Park!

00:29:12.981 --> 00:29:14.816
I'm sorry…

00:29:16.067 --> 00:29:17.652
I'm so sorry.

00:29:17.735 --> 00:29:19.696
-What…
-I'm so sorry.

00:29:23.157 --> 00:29:24.158
I'm sorry.

00:29:25.577 --> 00:29:27.120
Please forgive me.

00:29:28.204 --> 00:29:29.539
I'm sorry.

00:29:29.622 --> 00:29:32.166
If you give me just a little more time,

00:29:33.251 --> 00:29:36.212
I swear I'll fix everything.

00:29:36.296 --> 00:29:39.883
-Please forgive me.
-Hey, Mr. Park.

00:29:42.093 --> 00:29:43.970
Did you borrow money from thugs?

00:29:45.013 --> 00:29:47.140
-Oh, my.
-I can already tell.

00:29:48.641 --> 00:29:51.728
They're going to ruin
another small-time company.

00:29:54.022 --> 00:29:58.776
You put Tae-poong's items up
as collateral and sold them all off.

00:29:58.860 --> 00:30:01.195
And now you've even lost that too.

00:30:04.073 --> 00:30:07.952
Yes, you could say that.

00:30:09.871 --> 00:30:12.665
Were you scamming me then?

00:30:12.749 --> 00:30:14.208
I wasn't scamming you…

00:30:17.170 --> 00:30:18.421
I was just unlucky.

00:30:20.965 --> 00:30:23.593
Do you have any idea
what that money meant?

00:30:24.636 --> 00:30:26.804
I'm so sorry.

00:30:26.888 --> 00:30:28.681
Why me?

00:30:30.058 --> 00:30:31.351
Tell me.

00:30:31.434 --> 00:30:33.645
Why are you doing this to me?!

00:30:33.728 --> 00:30:35.647
Why? Seriously!

00:30:36.272 --> 00:30:40.276
I honestly took your money
to pay off an urgent interest bill,

00:30:41.653 --> 00:30:44.697
but I was going to make it up to you
once things improved.

00:30:45.782 --> 00:30:46.741
And?

00:30:46.824 --> 00:30:49.994
Since when did life go according to plan?

00:30:51.663 --> 00:30:53.581
In the meantime, the interest…

00:30:55.333 --> 00:30:57.377
How did it pile on so fast?

00:30:57.460 --> 00:30:58.586
Forget it.

00:30:59.212 --> 00:31:01.464
Forget about your debts and all that.

00:31:05.259 --> 00:31:06.260
What about my money?

00:31:08.096 --> 00:31:09.222
Where's my money?

00:31:09.305 --> 00:31:11.099
You took my down payment.

00:31:11.766 --> 00:31:14.018
That money
is the only reason I'm still alive.

00:31:21.317 --> 00:31:22.235
Damn it.

00:31:23.653 --> 00:31:27.615
Is there seriously
nothing left at all? Really?

00:31:28.449 --> 00:31:29.283
Damn it!

00:31:29.867 --> 00:31:31.577
There's absolutely nothing left?

00:31:33.830 --> 00:31:35.039
Do you have a plan?

00:31:35.915 --> 00:31:39.293
All the factories, shops, and banks

00:31:40.003 --> 00:31:40.837
took everything.

00:31:42.463 --> 00:31:44.048
There's no stock left at all.

00:31:44.841 --> 00:31:45.800
I think

00:31:47.385 --> 00:31:48.928
this will only end if I die.

00:31:50.763 --> 00:31:52.682
How dare you talk about dying?!

00:31:52.765 --> 00:31:55.977
Do you know who has
to pay your debt if you die?

00:31:58.938 --> 00:32:00.064
You can

00:32:01.691 --> 00:32:02.859
hit me too if you want.

00:32:04.861 --> 00:32:07.447
This bastard has completely lost his mind.

00:32:08.614 --> 00:32:10.700
Okay, fine. Come here.

00:32:10.783 --> 00:32:12.660
Come here, you bastard!

00:32:17.707 --> 00:32:18.583
Gosh.

00:32:19.417 --> 00:32:21.753
This is so frustrating.

00:32:23.629 --> 00:32:25.631
Hey! Tae-poong!

00:32:27.884 --> 00:32:31.220
-Where are you going?
-I'm going to report him to the police.

00:32:31.304 --> 00:32:35.349
That's not going to fix anything.
He doesn't even have electricity.

00:32:36.142 --> 00:32:39.353
My goodness.
Hold on. Let me make a few calls.

00:32:41.314 --> 00:32:42.565
Why did you take that?

00:32:43.733 --> 00:32:45.109
Just so I'd have something.

00:32:47.320 --> 00:32:48.696
This isn't worth much.

00:32:48.780 --> 00:32:50.448
PATENT CERTIFICATE

00:32:50.531 --> 00:32:52.909
You even got the patents.
What are we going to do now?

00:32:55.661 --> 00:32:57.080
You should call Mi-seon.

00:32:57.163 --> 00:32:58.664
Never mind, I'll do it.

00:33:04.420 --> 00:33:06.506
-Are you okay?
-Yes, of course.

00:33:07.340 --> 00:33:08.466
I'm fine.

00:33:12.053 --> 00:33:13.888
You're doing your best as the boss.

00:33:33.866 --> 00:33:38.162
BUSINESS ENGLISH CONVERSATION HANDBOOK

00:33:38.246 --> 00:33:40.998
TELL THEM THE QUALITY WILL BE DIFFERENT

00:34:08.901 --> 00:34:12.196
CONGRATULATIONS AND BEST WISHES

00:34:13.364 --> 00:34:15.324
Here's your beer, ma'am.

00:34:15.408 --> 00:34:16.284
Oh, my gosh!

00:34:17.034 --> 00:34:20.121
-What happened to your face?
-I got drunk and fell.

00:34:20.204 --> 00:34:23.583
-Be careful.
-Thank you.

00:34:23.666 --> 00:34:25.251
Be careful with that.

00:34:25.334 --> 00:34:28.462
-One spicy sea snail salad, please.
-Coming right up.

00:34:29.172 --> 00:34:31.883
You didn't have to bring anything.

00:34:31.966 --> 00:34:33.009
Thank you.

00:34:34.635 --> 00:34:36.679
You're amazing, Ms. Kim.

00:34:37.597 --> 00:34:41.893
How did you manage
to start a business right away?

00:34:42.768 --> 00:34:46.272
Not at all. I was scared,
so I opened up right next to the bank.

00:34:46.355 --> 00:34:48.149
They're my previous clients.

00:34:48.232 --> 00:34:50.443
-But still…
-Hello, Ms. Kim.

00:34:50.526 --> 00:34:53.404
Welcome, you can sit over there.

00:34:53.487 --> 00:34:57.074
-A bottle of soju, please.
-Coming right up.

00:35:00.286 --> 00:35:02.872
-Here you go.
-Can we get more of this?

00:35:02.955 --> 00:35:04.749
-You can get it yourself.
-Please.

00:35:04.832 --> 00:35:06.167
My goodness.

00:35:06.959 --> 00:35:10.379
-Can I see the menu, please?
-Where's the menu, Nam-mo?

00:35:11.172 --> 00:35:12.673
-It's over there.
-Okay.

00:35:30.733 --> 00:35:31.943
Tae-poong.

00:35:32.485 --> 00:35:35.821
What are you doing here?
You should've called.

00:35:35.905 --> 00:35:37.949
I waited for you.

00:35:38.032 --> 00:35:40.076
I'm sorry. The timing wasn't ideal.

00:35:40.993 --> 00:35:42.995
You must've waited long.

00:35:44.455 --> 00:35:48.376
-What's this? Fried chicken?
-Yes, it's for Beom.

00:35:48.459 --> 00:35:52.171
-We can't be the only ones who eat it.
-Good idea.

00:35:54.382 --> 00:35:55.466
This looks delicious.

00:35:58.427 --> 00:35:59.387
What's wrong?

00:36:01.347 --> 00:36:03.099
-Did something happen?
-No.

00:36:03.724 --> 00:36:07.019
Nothing happened. I'm just kind of tired.

00:36:08.396 --> 00:36:09.272
Okay.

00:36:10.481 --> 00:36:12.275
I'd be tired too, if I were you.

00:36:15.778 --> 00:36:19.949
Your mother didn't even realize
the house was being taken away,

00:36:20.950 --> 00:36:23.619
and she's living off her son at her age.

00:36:23.703 --> 00:36:25.871
Don't say that, Mom.

00:36:27.123 --> 00:36:28.249
But, son,

00:36:29.542 --> 00:36:31.168
don't try too hard.

00:36:34.547 --> 00:36:37.550
As long as I have you,
the whole world feels like home to me.

00:36:39.468 --> 00:36:40.553
And…

00:36:42.555 --> 00:36:47.101
I may be a good-for-nothing mom,
but you still have me.

00:36:48.352 --> 00:36:50.646
I won't ever let you go hungry.

00:36:52.523 --> 00:36:55.067
What I regret most in my life is…

00:36:59.864 --> 00:37:01.741
that I never once told…

00:37:04.577 --> 00:37:06.537
your father he could

00:37:07.997 --> 00:37:09.915
-lean on me.
-Come on.

00:37:11.375 --> 00:37:12.293
Mom.

00:37:14.795 --> 00:37:15.796
It's okay.

00:37:17.465 --> 00:37:20.009
I'm fine. I promise.

00:37:23.554 --> 00:37:25.639
-Tae-poong.
-Yes?

00:37:28.434 --> 00:37:29.852
You can lean on me.

00:37:32.563 --> 00:37:35.983
You can lean on me
when things become too tough.

00:37:37.818 --> 00:37:38.694
Okay?

00:37:50.373 --> 00:37:52.166
-Mom.
-Yes?

00:37:54.794 --> 00:37:56.379
I'm having such a hard time.

00:37:58.506 --> 00:37:59.965
It's been so hard.

00:38:02.593 --> 00:38:04.303
My goods are gone.

00:38:05.596 --> 00:38:07.181
They're gone,

00:38:08.682 --> 00:38:10.267
and all my money's gone too.

00:38:13.813 --> 00:38:18.651
I don't even know
where to start or what to do.

00:38:28.702 --> 00:38:29.787
I was…

00:38:33.707 --> 00:38:36.085
I was so scared because of that.

00:38:38.295 --> 00:38:39.505
It's okay.

00:38:41.006 --> 00:38:42.174
It's okay, sweetie.

00:38:57.481 --> 00:38:58.357
That's okay.

00:38:59.984 --> 00:39:01.193
It's okay, sweetie.

00:39:05.197 --> 00:39:07.199
CLEARANCE SALE

00:39:07.283 --> 00:39:09.743
BELLUA

00:39:09.827 --> 00:39:10.828
Hello.

00:39:15.708 --> 00:39:18.544
-How have you been?
-How did you know I was here?

00:39:18.627 --> 00:39:20.754
You told me you worked here that day.

00:39:22.214 --> 00:39:25.050
I've never seen
a woman drink so much beer.

00:39:25.885 --> 00:39:28.179
-What do you want?
-I'm here to repay you.

00:39:28.262 --> 00:39:31.474
-Forget it. Go back to your fried chicken.
-Just a minute.

00:39:31.557 --> 00:39:34.268
Today's my day off,
so I don't have to fry any chicken.

00:39:35.311 --> 00:39:37.396
It's cold today, isn't it?

00:39:37.480 --> 00:39:38.439
Here you go.

00:39:46.447 --> 00:39:47.865
It's cold. Take this.

00:39:50.075 --> 00:39:51.035
I don't want it.

00:39:54.413 --> 00:39:55.915
Woman No. 1, Oh Mi-ho.

00:39:56.916 --> 00:39:59.001
-Seriously?
-It's really cold.

00:39:59.835 --> 00:40:00.794
Isn't it warm?

00:40:02.505 --> 00:40:03.839
Stop following me.

00:40:06.509 --> 00:40:08.969
Sorry, he's not here yet.

00:40:10.137 --> 00:40:12.306
One moment. He just got home.

00:40:12.890 --> 00:40:14.892
Welcome back.

00:40:14.975 --> 00:40:16.310
Good night.

00:40:16.393 --> 00:40:18.395
You got a call from Pusan.

00:40:18.479 --> 00:40:19.438
-Pusan?
-Yes.

00:40:23.192 --> 00:40:25.361
-Hello, Ms. Jung?
-Yes, it's me.

00:40:25.444 --> 00:40:27.279
I found out who took the goods.

00:40:27.363 --> 00:40:28.489
You did?

00:40:28.572 --> 00:40:32.284
-Where is it?
-He's this loan shark I know.

00:40:33.244 --> 00:40:36.747
It's best not to do business
with him if you can help it.

00:40:36.830 --> 00:40:40.167
Anyway, I explained your situation

00:40:40.251 --> 00:40:42.086
and told him 500 pairs belonged to you.

00:40:42.169 --> 00:40:44.797
He'll return them
if you bring another five million won.

00:40:45.381 --> 00:40:46.757
So, who exactly

00:40:48.217 --> 00:40:49.051
has them?

00:40:49.635 --> 00:40:53.722
How can they take someone else's stuff
and then ask for money?

00:40:53.806 --> 00:40:54.932
Those goods are mine.

00:40:55.015 --> 00:40:59.103
Listen, half of it
is already useless and done with.

00:40:59.186 --> 00:41:01.438
If you don't want to do it,
you don't have to.

00:41:01.522 --> 00:41:02.356
No, I--

00:41:03.774 --> 00:41:06.610
Hello? This is Mi-seon, Ms. Jung.

00:41:06.694 --> 00:41:09.613
-How much did you say he wants?
-Five million won.

00:41:11.240 --> 00:41:12.283
Five million won…

00:41:13.450 --> 00:41:16.370
We'll call back once we get the money.

00:41:17.329 --> 00:41:18.330
Okay.

00:41:19.039 --> 00:41:21.542
Thank you. Good night.

00:41:22.876 --> 00:41:26.755
Don't worry about it, Ms. Oh.
We have no money.

00:41:27.298 --> 00:41:28.132
I'll handle it.

00:41:29.341 --> 00:41:30.384
What will you do?

00:41:31.760 --> 00:41:33.554
I'll go get the goods in person.

00:41:33.637 --> 00:41:36.890
You know what loan sharks are, right?

00:41:39.476 --> 00:41:42.021
And they might have priority of claims.

