You're saying I can't?

00:46:20.465 --> 00:46:22.050
All right. Thank you.

00:46:22.134 --> 00:46:23.802
SMALL BUSINESS SUPPORT CENTER
LOANS EMERGENCY

00:46:48.577 --> 00:46:51.622
SAVINGS ACCOUNT

00:46:52.414 --> 00:46:53.749
NAME: KANG TAE-POONG

00:47:00.547 --> 00:47:03.383
3,300,000 WON

00:47:06.887 --> 00:47:09.765
Can I get a yo-yo, Mi-seon?

00:47:10.849 --> 00:47:12.476
-Okay.
-All right!

00:47:22.944 --> 00:47:24.529
Oh, my.

00:47:24.613 --> 00:47:27.574
Who are all these people
that keep messing up?

00:47:28.825 --> 00:47:29.660
Son.

00:47:30.452 --> 00:47:32.204
What do you think failure is?

00:47:37.918 --> 00:47:39.211
Why, that…

00:47:40.921 --> 00:47:43.006
Something like the father of success?

00:47:43.090 --> 00:47:45.133
Failure is money.

00:47:45.842 --> 00:47:49.137
Someone needs to lose 100 won
for 100 won to be available.

00:47:50.305 --> 00:47:54.518
That's why failure
is a wonderful thing for people like us.

00:47:58.689 --> 00:48:01.191
These are safety shoes.

00:48:05.153 --> 00:48:06.113
Safety shoes?

00:48:09.658 --> 00:48:13.203
-I need you to go to Pusan.
-Pusan?

00:48:14.871 --> 00:48:16.081
I want you to fill this.

00:48:19.209 --> 00:48:20.043
Huh?

00:48:20.127 --> 00:48:22.879
PYO MERCHANT MARINE
TYPHOON TRADING

00:48:44.401 --> 00:48:47.070
TYPHOON TRADING

00:49:01.126 --> 00:49:04.129
-Weren't you busy today?
-I'm free now.

00:49:04.212 --> 00:49:08.341
-Why are you still here?
-I had some stuff to organize.

00:49:09.384 --> 00:49:11.219
And I'm going to Pusan tomorrow.

00:49:12.512 --> 00:49:13.472
Mr. Kang.

00:49:16.349 --> 00:49:18.101
Did you get the money?

00:49:18.769 --> 00:49:23.815
I tried asking a few places.
It's not easy, but I'll keep trying.

00:49:39.206 --> 00:49:40.123
What's this?

00:49:47.339 --> 00:49:48.215
What's this money?

00:49:48.799 --> 00:49:51.968
It's the account that you sent me by mail.

00:49:52.052 --> 00:49:55.597
-I added just a little bit more.
-I can't accept this.

00:49:56.890 --> 00:49:58.809
What's wrong with everyone?

00:49:59.518 --> 00:50:01.561
My dad wanted you to have that.

00:50:02.145 --> 00:50:04.815
I know. I appreciate
the thought behind it.

00:50:06.149 --> 00:50:07.150
But…

00:50:08.443 --> 00:50:11.029
This money really doesn't belong to me.

00:50:11.112 --> 00:50:13.406
I was thinking of returning it.

00:50:14.074 --> 00:50:17.828
Still, this doesn't feel right.
I'll figure it out.

00:50:17.911 --> 00:50:20.163
If I can't, we can try something else.

00:50:20.747 --> 00:50:21.998
Absolutely not.

00:50:22.082 --> 00:50:24.501
Go and get our goods back.

00:50:24.584 --> 00:50:27.087
Get them and we can sell them
for a bit more.

00:50:30.048 --> 00:50:31.466
We can do this.

00:51:05.959 --> 00:51:08.461
Stand tall. It's not the end of the world.

00:51:13.842 --> 00:51:14.926
Kang Tae-poong.

00:51:16.052 --> 00:51:20.265
The loan shark who
took your goods is Ryu Hui-gyu.

00:51:21.808 --> 00:51:25.979
Like I said last time,
that bastard isn't easy to deal with.

00:51:26.062 --> 00:51:27.314
He's ruthless.

00:51:27.397 --> 00:51:33.695
So just don't say a word,
give him the money and get the goods.

00:51:34.738 --> 00:51:35.655
That's it.

00:51:37.782 --> 00:51:38.783
Got it?

00:51:43.204 --> 00:51:44.122
Got it.

00:51:44.205 --> 00:51:48.084
I feel bad about what you went through,
so I'll help you up to this point.

00:51:49.336 --> 00:51:50.420
Understood?

00:51:53.298 --> 00:51:55.258
-Yes.
-Let's go.

00:52:08.146 --> 00:52:09.189
It's been a while.

00:52:17.364 --> 00:52:18.657
Not even a hello?

00:52:35.507 --> 00:52:36.549
What are you doing?

00:52:38.802 --> 00:52:39.636
Give me a light.

00:52:50.897 --> 00:52:53.233
You're taking on punks from Seoul now?

00:52:54.901 --> 00:52:56.236
I heard you had grown,

00:52:57.070 --> 00:52:58.738
but you're just the same as ever.

00:53:02.158 --> 00:53:05.036
You shouldn't mess with outsiders.

00:53:06.538 --> 00:53:07.372
Give it to him.

00:53:08.456 --> 00:53:10.834
We'll give it to you,
but only after we get ours.

00:53:11.543 --> 00:53:12.377
The goods?

00:53:14.004 --> 00:53:14.921
Follow me.

00:53:34.899 --> 00:53:36.735
Move it. Hurry it up.

00:53:36.818 --> 00:53:38.028
Yes, sir!

00:53:38.111 --> 00:53:40.363
We'll finish early if you guys hurry up.

00:53:41.823 --> 00:53:44.534
-You left out 500 of them, right?
-Yes, sir.

00:53:45.744 --> 00:53:47.704
-Leave out 500.
-So 500?

00:53:48.747 --> 00:53:50.665
If we leave out 500, it'll be 1,500.

00:53:51.666 --> 00:53:54.169
Let's just round it off to 30 million won.

00:53:59.299 --> 00:54:01.468
Look, it's Typhoon Trading!

00:54:02.385 --> 00:54:05.055
-Did you catch on?
-Wait a minute.

00:54:06.056 --> 00:54:08.224
Hold on. Manager Ha!

00:54:09.434 --> 00:54:10.393
What do you mean?

00:54:10.894 --> 00:54:12.937
Why are you leaving some of the goods?

00:54:18.359 --> 00:54:19.486
Tae-poong.

00:54:20.570 --> 00:54:21.988
This is good, but too spicy.

00:54:22.072 --> 00:54:24.657
Manager Ha, I can't eat it anymore.

00:54:25.575 --> 00:54:26.493
Let's keep moving.

00:54:27.285 --> 00:54:28.369
Hey.

00:54:30.705 --> 00:54:31.831
Are you a gangster now?

00:54:33.374 --> 00:54:37.629
Isn't it better to be poor
than a gangster?

00:54:37.712 --> 00:54:39.089
Have you lost your mind?

00:54:40.215 --> 00:54:43.968
Hey. Do you seriously think we're equals
just because I came here?

00:54:45.178 --> 00:54:47.931
You got any money? Or connections?

00:54:49.057 --> 00:54:51.226
Please stop!

00:54:51.309 --> 00:54:53.269
-Bring it on!
-No, don't.

00:54:53.353 --> 00:54:54.229
Bring it.

00:54:54.312 --> 00:54:55.855
Let's keep moving, guys.

00:54:55.939 --> 00:54:57.232
Let's get a move on.

00:54:57.315 --> 00:54:59.192
-That bum…
-Who are you calling a bum?

00:54:59.275 --> 00:55:01.236
Let's calm down, everyone.

00:55:01.319 --> 00:55:03.613
-You jerk.
-Just leave it.

00:55:03.696 --> 00:55:05.740
-You're nothing but a gangster.
-Bastard.

00:55:06.241 --> 00:55:09.077
-Stop.
-Watch your tongue!

00:55:09.160 --> 00:55:11.830
What the heck is this?

00:55:16.584 --> 00:55:17.961
Get this moving, now!

00:55:46.489 --> 00:55:49.033
Mister.

00:55:51.411 --> 00:55:52.370
Are you okay?

00:56:08.178 --> 00:56:11.097
You can't take a nap here.

00:56:13.558 --> 00:56:15.727
It's freezing in here, mister.

00:56:36.789 --> 00:56:39.417
-Is this fun to you?
-Yes. It's a lot of fun.

00:56:43.254 --> 00:56:44.714
Relax, you bastard.

00:56:46.925 --> 00:56:48.509
I'll kill you if you get in my way.

00:56:59.979 --> 00:57:03.233
SAFETY SHOES PERFORMANCE TESTING METHODS

00:57:24.003 --> 00:57:26.256
What's taking him so long?

00:57:38.518 --> 00:57:39.394
Take this.

00:57:44.107 --> 00:57:46.651
I can't give this money to these people.

00:57:47.360 --> 00:57:48.695
It's worth more than that.

00:57:49.946 --> 00:57:51.864
-What are you doing?
-Tae-poong.

00:57:51.948 --> 00:57:54.993
-You can't do this.
-You should go, Ms. Jung.

00:58:00.623 --> 00:58:01.708
Put your feet down.

00:58:02.417 --> 00:58:03.835
I said, put your feet down!

00:58:08.214 --> 00:58:09.090
Let's go.

00:58:11.884 --> 00:58:12.969
Listen to me.

00:58:13.052 --> 00:58:14.804
What good is looking at the ledger?

00:58:15.430 --> 00:58:16.806
You can't even sell an item.

00:58:20.977 --> 00:58:24.480
-How much does that guy owe you?
-Why do you want to know?

00:58:25.648 --> 00:58:26.774
It's 50 million won.

00:58:28.109 --> 00:58:31.738
-It's 70 million won now with interest.
-Make it 100 million.

00:58:34.907 --> 00:58:38.119
I'll sell 7,000 safety shoes
and give you 100 million won.

00:58:39.537 --> 00:58:41.331
Thirty million won for a dump sale?

00:58:44.042 --> 00:58:46.544
If you're clueless,
even a diamond is just a rock.

00:58:48.880 --> 00:58:49.714
Is that so?

00:58:51.382 --> 00:58:52.925
It's a great offer,

00:58:54.344 --> 00:58:55.595
but there's already a buyer.

00:58:56.429 --> 00:58:57.805
Who? Me?

00:58:59.807 --> 00:59:01.726
What happens if he can't do it?

00:59:02.602 --> 00:59:03.853
Then I'll take the interest.

00:59:08.483 --> 00:59:10.818
Mr. Park's life is a given, of course.

00:59:12.945 --> 00:59:16.908
DEBT ACKNOWLEDGEMENT FORM
COLLATERAL: TWO EYEBALLS

00:59:22.872 --> 00:59:23.748
So,

00:59:25.750 --> 00:59:27.627
can you put your eyes on the line?

00:59:28.503 --> 00:59:30.421
Don't do this. Don't do this, Tae-poong.

00:59:32.423 --> 00:59:37.136
This is unbelievable.
I'll back off if you're that desperate.

00:59:37.220 --> 00:59:38.221
On one condition.

00:59:39.180 --> 00:59:42.225
You have to let me gouge out
one of that bastard's eyes.

00:59:48.272 --> 00:59:49.232
What's wrong?

00:59:50.942 --> 00:59:51.984
You scared?

00:59:55.113 --> 00:59:56.364
You have to swear

00:59:57.365 --> 01:00:00.076
to leave us alone
once you get 100 million won.

01:00:02.912 --> 01:00:03.830
What's wrong?

01:00:05.540 --> 01:00:06.541
You scared?

01:00:09.752 --> 01:00:11.129
Bring the ink pad.

01:00:19.512 --> 01:00:23.099
DEBT ACKNOWLEDGE FORM

01:00:25.977 --> 01:00:26.978
What's your name?

01:00:33.735 --> 01:00:35.069
That's none of your business.

01:00:40.116 --> 01:00:41.367
I'm just a trader…

01:00:45.079 --> 01:00:46.330
from Typhoon Trading.

01:01:19.530 --> 01:01:26.496
HEAVEN, WHERE WE ARE

01:02:00.363 --> 01:02:02.782
TYPHOON FAMILY

01:02:02.865 --> 01:02:04.575
Do we have to try so hard?

01:02:04.659 --> 01:02:08.287
I want to show them
our goods and our good taste.

01:02:08.371 --> 01:02:10.915
She's smiling. Does she like Tae-poong?

01:02:10.998 --> 01:02:13.251
Those sparkly eyes of yours.

01:02:13.334 --> 01:02:15.336
They'll be mine in a month.

01:02:15.419 --> 01:02:16.921
What's he talking about?

01:02:17.004 --> 01:02:18.589
We're not a rescue organization.

01:02:18.673 --> 01:02:20.383
We're a trading company!

01:02:20.466 --> 01:02:22.385
What now?
Why can't you load our shoes?

01:02:22.468 --> 01:02:24.262
Give me all you've got.

01:02:24.345 --> 01:02:26.389
Are you nervous? I'm not nervous at all.

01:02:27.390 --> 01:02:29.684
You're the best trader in our company.

